"{\"uid\": \"www.gatewayhouse.in.-dislocations-brexit-can-india-gain--Part2\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Rover), IT companies like Tech Mahindra, and mining giant Vedanta Resources - which together generate a turnover of \\u00a319 billion[6] ($25.4 billion) from their UK-based operations.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tech_Mahindra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tech Mahindra\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tech_Mahindra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tech_Mahindra\"}, {\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vedanta_Resources\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vedanta Resources\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vedanta_Resources\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vedanta_Resources\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These may now be forced to open additional offices in the Continent.\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be additional costs, but it is no longer a hardship since English is becoming the operating language of most multinational firms.\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then there is India's old friend Russia, which is likely to be less isolated in Europe as a result of the Brexit.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not surprisingly, Russia is the only major power that welcomed the referendum result.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moscow has been cornered by the eastward expansion of NATO and sanctions imposed by the EU after the annexation of the Crimea by Russia.\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it might be premature for Russia to celebrate because while the economic arm of this alliance - the EU - has stumbled, the military arm - the NATO - could draw ever closer in the face of this political and economic crisis.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The upcoming NATO summit in Warsaw starting on 8 July will lay out NATO's future thrust[7].\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the UK out of the Union, Europe, especially Germany, can revert to a relationship determined by geoeconomics realities rather than Anglo-Saxon hostilities against Russia.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Russia that is under less pressure is strategically more valuable for India because it reduces the incentive for Moscow to compromise defence, nuclear power and space technology co-operation between the two countries.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Specifically, it also lowers the appeal for a cash-strapped Moscow from playing junior partner of a cash-rich China since Beijing is becoming a bigger consumer of Russian gas exports than Europe.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now is the time for India to cement its relationship with Russia by overt gestures like further increasing its stake in Moscow's energy sector and by signing a major arms deal with it.\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the important issue of trade.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apart from the need for the UK to negotiate individual bilateral Free Trade Agreements (FTAs) with the remaining 27 countries in the EU, Brexit also complicates the ongoing Transatlantic Trade & Investment Pact (TTIP) negotiations between the U.S. and the EU.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The repudiation of the Trans Pacific Partnership (TPP) by the leading candidates for the U.S. Presidential election of 2016 - Hillary Clinton, Donald Trump and Bernie Sanders - as well as the U.S. government's threat that the UK would be at the back of the queue for a separate trade agreement with it, can be an impetus for reviving the stalled World Trade Organisation, which is at least a global system, and bilateral FTA's.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"India can, therefore, leverage this opening by speedily concluding an advantageous bilateral trade treaty with the UK, since commerce between the two is worth over $14 billion[8] in 2015-16 and India is among the top three investors in the UK in recent years.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also possible that Brexit could make the EU's negotiating stance more flexible, becoming an opportunity for India to seal the almost decade-old negotiations for the EU-India free trade deal.\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So far the EU has held the FTA hostage to India-Italy bilateral differences and insistence on duty cuts for its auto and wine exports to India.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Conversely, the Indian government has reviewed existing FTAs and concluded that they need to be renegotiated because the country has gained little in terms of increased market access.\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All said, if like the UK's Brexiteers who opted out of the EU, an angry and increasingly disillusioned American electorate endorse Donald J Trump's inward-looking Presidency in November, then Beijing will surely pounce on the opportunities that Brexit has spawned.\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If India\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3618, \"entities\": []}]}"